==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lengthen
<hw>Length"en</hw> <pr>(-'n)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Lengthened</conjf> <pr>(-'nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Lengthening</conjf> <pr>(-'n*⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<def>To extent in length; to make longer in extent or duration; <as>as,
to <ex>lengthen</ex> a line or a road; to <ex>lengthen</ex> life; --
sometimes followed by <ptcl>out</ptcl>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What if I please to <qex>lengthen</qex> out his date.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lengthen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lengthen
<hw>Length"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become longer.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lengthful</ent>⟦br⟧
